{
  "texts": [
    "However, the influence of power dynamics between patients and investigators is often not fully addressed within the consent process.",
    "However, in clinical QP contexts, consent requirements can vary.",
    "Some institutions implement AI technology as part of routine QP activities without obtaining explicit consent for each use, instead relying on broader policies and general consent from patients for treatment and quality assurance 9.",
    "Currently, there is no universally agreed-upon ethical or legal requirement to disclose the use of medical AI for informed consent in the United States, the European Union, or South Korea 8, 9.",
    "The approach to consent varies by hospital policies, legal requirements, and ethical guidelines 33."
  ]
}